description: Dormammu, Ikonn, Tiboro, Ningal, the Dweller in Darkness, names to conjure with...literally! Yet they're only a few of the occult enemies who confront Stephen Strange, Sorcerer Supreme, challenged by Baron Mordo, the Eye Killers, and sorcerers from across the world and throughout the dimensions! Weirdness awaits in the Realm of the Shadowqueen and an unfallen Roman Empire, but with Nightmare and D'Spayre around, the human psyche may be the deadliest battleground of all! Plus the mystery of Murdoch Adams, Monster Hunter! With the Man-Thing, Brother Voodoo, and Namor the Sub-Mariner, plus the Avengers, the Fantastic Four, and the Howling Commandos! Featuring rare horror work by genre legend Howard Chaykin! Collects Doctor Strange (1974-1987 2nd Series) #30-56, Chamber of Chills (1972-1976) #4, and Man-Thing (1974-1975) #4.
name: Volume 4

description: In this issue of UltraVixen #2 we rejoin our female heroine as she continues her search for the missing fusion engines which were stolen last issue. Unbeknownst to our heroine the nefarious S.C.O.R.P.I.O has plans for the advanced technology, plans that will rock UltraVixen to her core. Catch a glimpse at her personal life and the struggles of being the child of golden age Meteor City heroes in this action packed issue!
name: Ultravixen Vs Mommy Dearest

description: After surviving the Kill-House exercise (from Issue #1), Krossfire is immediately deployed into the field on another Ghost Squadron mission…this time an ex-Ghost Squadron member, Eon Marshall, is rampaging through a sector of New Metropolis with his bio-designed mutant monster, the Termantis, destroying everything in sight. Reservoir is on the scene to attempt to slow down the destruction, but soon finds out that the Termantis mutant is able to absorb energy from weapons and shooting it only makes it grow faster and stronger. Will all of New Metropolis be laid to waste…in MARSHALL LAW?
name: Marshall Law
The Fury of the War God

description: Featuring tales of the macabre and suspense starring the Living Mummy, Brother Voodoo, Gabriel the Devil Hunter, Golem, Scarecro, Modred the Mystic, and many more! A voodoo virtuoso. A devil-tainted demi-druid. A half-mad minister. A creature of the crypts, a man-mountain of marble and a giddy giggling ghoul - these are the horrific heroes who protect the world from forces even more frightening than themselves! Demons, zombies, warlocks and terrorists - all in these nightmarish narratives from the shocking scarefest of the seventies! Guest-starring Spider-Man, Spider-Woman and the Thing!
name: Volume Two
